02:15:20.512 --> 02:15:23.141
Sometimes
even spies fall in love.

02:15:26.986 --> 02:15:28.749
We can protect him.

02:15:29.221 --> 02:15:30.746
Make him safe.

02:15:31.156 --> 02:15:33.523
Nobody would know,
not even him.

02:15:37.096 --> 02:15:39.656
All it would require
is for you

02:15:41.734 --> 02:15:43.099
to help us

02:15:44.436 --> 02:15:46.427
when your help is needed.

02:16:01.286 --> 02:16:03.118
I thought
you'd like to see this.

02:16:07.626 --> 02:16:09.651
She's a very pretty girl.

02:16:10.796 --> 02:16:13.424
It's easy to see
why he fell for her.

02:16:29.448 --> 02:16:32.884
I know it's an extremely
difficult situation for you.

02:16:37.222 --> 02:16:40.316
But I'm afraid I'm going to
need your answer very soon.

02:16:43.195 --> 02:16:44.754
You must decide

02:16:46.498 --> 02:16:48.967
what is of more importance
to you.

02:16:50.769 --> 02:16:52.430
Your country or...

02:16:56.941 --> 02:16:58.376
Or your son.

02:17:28.707 --> 02:17:30.539
She's not
who you think she is.

02:17:32.745 --> 02:17:34.975
She's not a friendly, Edward.

02:17:35.614 --> 02:17:37.412
I don't believe you.

02:17:37.883 --> 02:17:40.147
Why should I believe you?

02:17:40.486 --> 02:17:43.352
You told me yourself
not to trust anybody.

02:17:44.388 --> 02:17:47.120
You're the master
at creating the truth.

02:17:48.960 --> 02:17:50.360
I love her.

02:17:51.096 --> 02:17:52.825
I've asked her
to marry me.

02:17:53.298 --> 02:17:55.129
I will not let you
take that away from me.

02:17:55.267 --> 02:17:57.602
I can't protect you anymore,
I can't keep you safe.

02:17:57.602 --> 02:17:58.695
Safe?

02:18:01.206 --> 02:18:03.402
Safe? I never felt safe.

02:18:03.674 --> 02:18:04.941
I was always frightened.

02:18:04.942 --> 02:18:08.079
I always lived in fear that something
awful was going to happen to you.

02:18:08.080 --> 02:18:10.013
Or if not,
to Mother or to me.

02:18:10.014 --> 02:18:13.110
I was always afraid, because
everything was a secret.

02:19:32.397 --> 02:19:33.496
Edward.

02:19:33.498 --> 02:19:35.900
Hello, may I come in?
Yes. Of course.

02:19:35.901 --> 02:19:37.834
Is everything all right?

02:19:38.870 --> 02:19:40.638
I was on my way home
from work

02:19:40.638 --> 02:19:43.941
and I had this overwhelming
desire to hear you play the violin.

02:19:43.941 --> 02:19:45.568
Play the violin? But...

02:19:46.712 --> 02:19:49.681
Edward, I'm so tired. Can't
this wait until tomorrow?

02:19:49.915 --> 02:19:52.247
I'd appreciate it
if you'd play it now.

02:19:53.518 --> 02:19:54.577
Now?

02:23:08.914 --> 02:23:11.610
I just wanted to hear something
from you that was true.

02:23:21.860 --> 02:23:23.487
He was careless.

02:23:23.962 --> 02:23:26.522
FBI. You're under arrest.
Stand up.

02:23:28.467 --> 02:23:30.401
Didn't learn how to
hide in plain sight.

02:23:30.802 --> 02:23:32.670
Where are they taking me?

02:23:32.671 --> 02:23:35.572
I can't go home! You know
they can't trust me anymore!

02:23:36.074 --> 02:23:37.906
You know
what they will do to me!

02:23:38.243 --> 02:23:39.574
Sorry, Edward.

02:23:41.146 --> 02:23:43.478
I truly did like you.

02:23:44.916 --> 02:23:48.944
I mean it. In another world, we actually
would have been quite good friends.

02:23:52.290 --> 02:23:54.122
Are you still there, Mother?

02:23:54.326 --> 02:23:56.590
Your worst fear has come true.

02:24:01.099 --> 02:24:02.931
Alone and friendless

02:24:05.070 --> 02:24:07.232
without a country of your own.

02:25:19.578 --> 02:25:22.342
We have a whole new place
to fight over.

02:25:24.549 --> 02:25:25.915
The stars.

02:25:30.789 --> 02:25:32.188
Your offer.

02:25:35.827 --> 02:25:37.420
I have to decline.

02:25:48.440 --> 02:25:52.240
You've succeeded in stopping
us from taking back Cuba.

02:25:55.914 --> 02:25:57.746
The damage is done.

02:26:00.852 --> 02:26:03.185
There's no need for you
to hurt my son.

02:26:09.761 --> 02:26:12.025
Let's just leave it
between you and me.

02:26:16.434 --> 02:26:17.766
Very well.

02:26:19.738 --> 02:26:21.171
I will wait.

02:26:23.274 --> 02:26:25.334
But there will come a time

02:26:27.278 --> 02:26:30.043
when I will ask you to help me
with a problem

02:26:31.116 --> 02:26:35.052
that wouldn't cost you much
but be of some value to me.

02:26:38.690 --> 02:26:41.284
You never know
what the future will bring.

02:26:43.895 --> 02:26:47.195
Friends can be enemies,
and enemies friends.

02:27:04.082 --> 02:27:05.379
This girl,

02:27:07.719 --> 02:27:10.279
neither of us
can be sure about her.

02:27:14.092 --> 02:27:17.062
But she's about to be
a part of your family.

02:27:19.831 --> 02:27:21.629
I believe in family.

02:27:26.905 --> 02:27:29.738
You want her to be
a part of your family,

02:27:31.376 --> 02:27:32.707
don't you?

02:27:57.736 --> 02:27:59.670
It was good to see you.

02:28:02.073 --> 02:28:05.737
We will talk again,
my dear friend.

02:28:14.419 --> 02:28:15.819
Sorry to bother.

02:28:15.820 --> 02:28:18.983
I want to buy a little souvenir to
my daughter. They have no change.

02:28:20.625 --> 02:28:21.925
What does it cost?

02:28:21.926 --> 02:28:23.417
It costs a dollar.

02:28:25.396 --> 02:28:29.163
Here. It's a gift. Regards from
the United States government.

02:28:30.268 --> 02:28:33.101
It's a cardinal rule
to be generous in a democracy.

02:28:38.176 --> 02:28:39.439
Thank you.

02:29:33.364 --> 02:29:35.199
So where is she?

02:29:35.200 --> 02:29:37.000
We're gonna meet her
at the church.

02:29:37.001 --> 02:29:40.003
I can't wait to meet her. You'll
love her. You're gonna love her.

02:29:42.907 --> 02:29:44.568
Yes, that's good.

02:29:59.791 --> 02:30:01.190
Come on in.

02:30:10.401 --> 02:30:12.028
Hello, Margaret.

02:30:16.541 --> 02:30:19.306
Let's celebrate.
I'll get some champagne.

02:30:26.684 --> 02:30:28.448
How was the flight?

02:30:30.822 --> 02:30:32.255
It was long.

02:30:42.133 --> 02:30:44.466
How do you like
living in Phoenix?

02:30:48.206 --> 02:30:50.265
It's the first time
I've slept in years.

02:30:54.779 --> 02:30:56.110
Here we go.

02:31:21.839 --> 02:31:23.171
To your happiness.

02:31:23.408 --> 02:31:24.739
To your happiness.

02:33:12.250 --> 02:33:13.683
Your wife...

02:33:14.185 --> 02:33:15.949
What have you done?

02:33:17.722 --> 02:33:19.918
Will you go inside, Mother?

02:33:21.459 --> 02:33:23.120
Go inside, Mom.

02:33:24.896 --> 02:33:27.387
Please, just go in the church.

02:33:37.608 --> 02:33:39.342
She's pregnant.

02:33:57.728 --> 02:33:59.560
You couldn't...
You couldn't have.

02:34:01.032 --> 02:34:02.727
You couldn't.
No.

02:34:03.701 --> 02:34:05.362
I love you.

02:34:06.437 --> 02:34:08.201
I love you
so much.

02:34:32.764 --> 02:34:34.493
Mr. Wilson?
Mr. Hayes.

02:34:35.566 --> 02:34:38.092
Have you been here before,
Mother? No, I haven't.

02:34:39.137 --> 02:34:41.037
Whose idea was that?

02:34:41.305 --> 02:34:42.898
It's classified.

02:34:45.943 --> 02:34:48.640
Mr. Allen has notified
the President he'll resign.

02:34:50.715 --> 02:34:53.275
Something about
Swiss bank accounts.

02:34:55.153 --> 02:34:56.520
Where did these
come from?

02:34:56.521 --> 02:35:00.116
They were in the car. I thought
you had them sent down, sir.

02:35:00.324 --> 02:35:04.193
Seems the greedy bastard has
been hiding money away for years.

02:35:04.595 --> 02:35:08.623
Whoever had the statements sent them
to him in a box of Swiss chocolates.

02:35:11.402 --> 02:35:13.302
It wasn't you, was it?

02:35:16.340 --> 02:35:18.175
The President's asked me
to become Director

02:35:18.176 --> 02:35:20.777
and do a complete
housecleaning at my discretion.

02:35:20.778 --> 02:35:22.269
I need someone I can trust.

02:35:22.713 --> 02:35:25.080
After all,
we're still brothers.

02:35:27.084 --> 02:35:29.485
This building
doesn't get built without you.

02:35:29.854 --> 02:35:32.016
You're CIA's heart and soul.

02:35:32.857 --> 02:35:36.885
Who knows, you might have a secret
about me in that safe of yours.

02:35:38.763 --> 02:35:43.530
This whole wing will be your part
of the world. Counterintelligence.

02:35:44.302 --> 02:35:47.037
Take a look around.
I've got an oversight meeting.

02:35:47.038 --> 02:35:50.701
Can you imagine? They think
they can look into our closet.

02:35:51.142 --> 02:35:52.803
As if we'll let them.

02:35:56.314 --> 02:35:58.783
I remember
a senator once asked me

02:35:59.450 --> 02:36:03.444
when we talk about CIA, why we never
use the word "the" in front of it.

02:36:04.388 --> 02:36:07.984
And I asked him, "Do you put
the word 'the' in front of God?"

02:36:57.208 --> 02:36:59.472
"They are right
what they say about me.

02:37:00.511 --> 02:37:03.481
"I was weak. A coward.

02:37:07.051 --> 02:37:08.951
"I compromised myself.

02:37:09.720 --> 02:37:12.883
"My honor. My family.
My country.

02:37:16.294 --> 02:37:18.285
"I am ashamed of myself.

02:37:20.197 --> 02:37:23.531
"To my wife, I am sorry
I've done this to you.

02:37:26.137 --> 02:37:27.627
"To my son,

02:37:28.306 --> 02:37:31.241
"I hope you will grow to be
a courageous man.

02:37:32.076 --> 02:37:34.977
"A good husband.
A good father.

02:37:41.719 --> 02:37:45.587
"I hope whatever you decide to
do, you lead a good, full life.

02:37:51.195 --> 02:37:54.631
"I hope whatever
your dreams may be come true.

02:37:58.202 --> 02:38:00.603
"Your loving husband
and father. "

